1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:02,160
(Title: Saebit Day Plans,
Bazaar, New Light Prince)

2
00:00:04,799 --> 00:00:07,839
Okay, guys. At the count of three,

3
00:00:07,879 --> 00:00:09,970
you're going to choose someone, okay?

4
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:20,760
One, two,

5
00:00:22,359 --> 00:00:23,399
three.

6
00:00:33,079 --> 00:00:36,600
What are you doing, Shin-Woo?
Do you want to be the prince?

7
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:49,920
Yes!

8
00:00:50,039 --> 00:00:51,320
Then, with a unanimous vote,

9
00:00:51,359 --> 00:00:54,159
the participant for the New Light
Prince Contest this year will be...

10
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:57,399
Woo Tae-Gyeong!
Give him a round of applause.

11
00:00:57,439 --> 00:00:58,920
Congratulations, Tae-Gyeong.

12
00:01:00,280 --> 00:01:01,479
No way.

13
00:01:10,799 --> 00:01:12,120
(Saebit Boy High School Meeting)

14
00:01:12,879 --> 00:01:15,239
You guys planned it...

15
00:01:15,769 --> 00:01:17,200
while I was in the bathroom, right?

16
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:19,159
You agreed to choose me, right?

17
00:01:20,689 --> 00:01:23,560
What are you talking about?
What do you take us for?

18
00:01:23,719 --> 00:01:25,879
When you were in the bathroom,
we didn't do anything.

19
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,680
We just sat here.

20
00:01:27,719 --> 00:01:28,920
Right, Shin-Woo?

21
00:01:37,439 --> 00:01:38,439
I'm sorry.

22
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:42,200
I knew it.

23
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:45,640
We need good teamwork to pull off a con.

24
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,239
Why are your ears so red?

25
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:49,120
They're like a lie detector test.

26
00:01:49,239 --> 00:01:50,920
That's why I told you
we shouldn't do it.

27
00:01:50,959 --> 00:01:52,159
I'm sorry, Tae-Gyeong.

28
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:54,640
But it's because you're the only person
that can do it.

29
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:57,799
But what's the New Light Prince?

30
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:59,040
Well...

31
00:01:59,079 --> 00:02:02,400
Saebit Day is the charity event
hosted by Saebit Foundation.

32
00:02:02,439 --> 00:02:05,920
During that event, the part
that raises the most donations is...

33
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:10,039
the New Light Prince Contest.
That's what they say.

34
00:02:10,090 --> 00:02:12,840
If I were to give you more details,
it's exactly what it sounds like.

35
00:02:12,879 --> 00:02:15,400
They choose the most handsome
and popular person for it.

36
00:02:15,439 --> 00:02:18,039
It's tradition for someone
in the student council to do it.

37
00:02:18,370 --> 00:02:21,400
Da-On, who couldn't make it
because of his exams,

38
00:02:21,439 --> 00:02:22,919
won last year.

39
00:02:25,159 --> 00:02:27,000
It was incredible back then.

40
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:33,960
In any case,
the New Light Prince this year...

41
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:36,090
will be Tae-Gyeong.

42
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:38,319
He's very handsome, just like me.

43
00:02:40,530 --> 00:02:42,240
What are you talking about?

44
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,120
Why are you worried, Tae-Gyeong?

45
00:02:44,159 --> 00:02:45,680
I'm sure you will win.

46
00:02:45,719 --> 00:02:48,759
The best stylist ever, me, Namkung,
will help you,

47
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,919
so don't worry.

48
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,680
You don't have to wear your uniform.

49
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:55,599
I have to prepare an outfit
and go on stage all by myself?

50
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:57,879
I'm really bad at that.

51
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,759
Don't worry about that.

52
00:03:01,199 --> 00:03:04,599
You will have a manager
to help you with everything.

53
00:03:04,639 --> 00:03:06,000
Who is it?

54
00:03:06,159 --> 00:03:09,199
It's Noh Shin-Woo.

55
00:03:10,039 --> 00:03:11,039
What?

56
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:14,199
Shin-Woo will be Prince Tae-Gyeong's...

57
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,680
manager.

58
00:03:15,719 --> 00:03:17,719
Give him a round of applause.

59
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,400
That's a great idea.

60
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:21,080
This is great, Tae-Gyeong.

61
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:25,120
Right.

62
00:03:31,039 --> 00:03:33,039
Do you have time tomorrow?

63
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,360
Yes, of course.

64
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:39,560
Then do you want to meet at
K Shopping Mall at 12 tomorrow?

65
00:03:41,039 --> 00:03:42,120
Sure.

66
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:46,599
What about lunch?
Are you going to eat first?

67
00:03:46,879 --> 00:03:49,520
No. Let's eat together.

68
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:51,639
Okay.

69
00:03:53,319 --> 00:03:54,960
- Also...
- What?

70
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,479
What are you going to wear tomorrow?

71
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:00,599
Why are you asking me about that?

72
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:03,599
I'm going to be dressed
in an effortlessly chic look.

73
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,919
What does it mean
to be effortlessly chic?

74
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:10,560
I'm just going to wear whatever I see.

75
00:04:11,199 --> 00:04:13,759
How have you never heard of
the effortlessly chic look?

76
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:14,960
Is that so wrong?

77
00:04:15,039 --> 00:04:17,120
Everyone these days knows what that is.

78
00:04:17,170 --> 00:04:19,800
- Do you know everything?
- Of course I do.

79
00:04:19,839 --> 00:04:21,519
Plus, I'm not a picky eater.

80
00:04:28,050 --> 00:04:30,120
Da-On. What are you doing?

81
00:04:31,279 --> 00:04:32,680
Is that for me?

82
00:04:33,959 --> 00:04:36,839
- What?
- Nothing. I'm just kidding.

83
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,240
Let's go eat
in the student council room.

84
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,800
(Chats, Noh Shin-Woo)

85
00:04:52,839 --> 00:04:55,079
(Tae-Gyeong leave the chatroom.
Leave. Did you do it?)

86
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:57,439
(I'm not going to do it.)

87
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,240
Is he ignoring me?

88
00:05:25,399 --> 00:05:28,120
(Enter search words.)

89
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,759
(The meaning of effortlessly chic)

90
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,879
(It means you're dressed up
but not too dressed up.)

91
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:34,040
(Dressed up but not too dressed up)

92
00:05:35,959 --> 00:05:38,759
"Dressed up but not too dressed up"?

93
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:40,399
(The meaning of effortlessly chic)

94
00:05:40,759 --> 00:05:42,079
What does that mean?

95
00:05:45,399 --> 00:05:46,879
(Tae-Gyeong: Don't be late tomorrow.)

96
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:48,519
(Tae-Gyeong)

97
00:05:57,319 --> 00:05:59,920
(Don't be late tomorrow.)

98
00:05:59,959 --> 00:06:01,040
He's ignoring me again?

99
00:06:01,079 --> 00:06:03,360
(Go to bed.)

100
00:06:03,399 --> 00:06:04,399
Wait.

101
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,439
Darn it.

102
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,720
I read it right away.

103
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,199
What if he thinks I was waiting
for his text?

104
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:36,680
"How to go on a nice date".

105
00:06:38,199 --> 00:06:40,319
(The first tip
on having a successful date.)

106
